      "writtenOn": "2017-12-04T21:43:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This (and all other reads in this method) should be serviced by a subrange reader that makes sure you don’t go out of the segment’s bounds.\n\nIt may make the most sense to set up the subrange reader in NextNote() when you advance to a new PT_NOTE segment. This ProcessMemoryRange could also be used in place of segment_end_address_.\n\nUsing the subrange reader would allow you to get rid of the custom overflow detection in this method: you could just let Read() fail, log something for you, and all you’d have to do is return kError (which you’re already doing anyway).",
      "revId": "772202373065cc8d86fccb8240edc90c3a73c1d9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
